column1: Why was the baby strawberry crying? Because its parents were in a jam. Poor little thing
Why did the chicken cross the playground? To get to the other slide. It wanted to have some fun!
What do you call a snowman with a six – pack? An abdominal snowman. He’s the fittest snowman around!
Why don’t seagulls fly over the bay? Because then they’d be bagels. That would be a strange transformation!
Why did the coffee file a police report? It got mugged. That’s a tough break for the poor coffee
What do you call a fake stone in Ireland? A sham – rock. It’s a sneaky little rock!
Why did the belt go to jail? For holding up pants. It was a fashion – related crime.
What’s a foot long and slippery? A slipper. It’s a dangerous little footwear!
Why can’t a nose be 18 inches long? Because then it would be a yard. That’s a huge nose!
What do you call a boomerang that doesn’t come back? A stick. It’s just a regular old stick now.
Why was the math book unhappy? Because it had too many problems. And it couldn’t find the answers on its own.
What’s the best day to go to the beach? Sunday
column3: because it’s a sand – day. It’s the perfect day for some sun and sand.

column1: Why did the golfer wear two pairs of pants? In case he got a hole in one. You never know what might happen on the green!
What do you call a cow with no legs? Ground beef. It’s a meaty transformation!
Why don’t oysters share their pearls? Because they’re shellfish. They’re just too selfish with their treasures.
Why did the scarecrow win an award? Because he was outstanding in his field. He really was the best in his area.
